# Calendar/Event Planner CLI App

A command-line interface (CLI) application for managing events and users in a calendar/event planner.

## Features

 Create, list, and manage events with details such as title, description, date, time, location, and category.
 Create user accounts with usernames and email addresses.
 Manage event categories.
 Set event reminders.
 Search for events based on various criteria.
### tecnologies used
Python: The core programming language used to build the CLI application.

SQLite: A lightweight relational database management system used to store event and user data.

SQLAlchemy: A Python SQL toolkit and Object-Relational Mapping (ORM) library used for database interaction and modeling.

Click: A Python package used for creating command-line interfaces (CLIs). It simplifies the process of defining and handling command-line commands and options.



## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

 Python 3.8+
-SQLite database (included by default)

### Installation

 Clone the repository:

   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/levina23/your-calendar-app.git

### Navigate to the project directory:
cd your-calendar-app

### Install the required Python packages:
pip install -r requirements.txt

### Usage
# Commands
List events;
python cli.py list-events
python cli.py create-user
python cli.py create-event
python cli.py create-category

### Development
To add new commands, define functions using the @cli.command() decorator in cli.py.
Write unit tests and integration tests using a testing framework like pytest.

